text: Ana Ambrazienė (14 April 1955 – 12 February 2025) was a Lithuanian hurdler. She was born in Vilnius. She represented the Soviet Union in the 1970s and 1980s. She won a silver medal at the World Athletics Championships in 1983. Ambrazienė died on 12 February 2025 in Vilnius at the age of 69. ==References== Category:1955 births Category:2025 deaths Category:Hurdlers Category:Lithuanian sportspeople Category:People from Vilnius
